# Variable naming

Use **clear, concise names** for variables. **Do not use single-character names** in any case.

- Improves readability and makes intent obvious.
- No exceptions: use descriptive names for loop indices, callbacks, destructuring, and everywhere else.

```typescript
// ❌ BAD
const d = await getData();
items.map(x => x.id);
for (let i = 0; i < arr.length; i++) { ... }

// ✅ GOOD
const data = await getData();
items.map(item => item.id);
for (let index = 0; index < arr.length; index++) { ... }
```

Keep names short but meaningful (e.g. `user`, `count`, `isLoading`).
